text = "How to train your Agent ...

Just click on the \"train your Agent\" button and it wil undergo 10,000 
training episodes, then save the file as your trained policy so the
Agent can access it to move in the environment.  
The trainig algorithm is a very basic Q-Learning algorithm that is
entirely within Godot's GD Script.  ... Very cool.  !!
This was made possible by \"pseudo-dividing\" the environment 
into 22 cells. Watch the video to see how it works.  
This method can be expanded to encompass more complicated
environments, but be careful !! ...  It is a lot of work to designate
the movements into and out of each cell, and to get it working.  "

